<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="type locality">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type locality.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
&quot;near Dum-Dum, Calcutta&quot; [= Dumdum, Kolkata, West Bengal, India] (
<bibRefCitation author="Prashad, B" journalOrPublisher="Nature in Singapore" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://faunaofindia.nic.in/PDFVolumes/memoirs/008/02/0069-0089.pdf" refId="B26" refString="Prashad, B, 1925. Revision of the Indian Ampullariidae. Memoirs of the Indian Museum 8(2): 69-89, pls. 13-15. http://faunaofindia.nic.in/PDFVolumes/memoirs/008/02/0069-0089.pdf" title="Revision of the Indian Ampullariidae. Memoirs of the Indian Museum 8 (2): 69 - 89, pls. 13 - 15." url="http://faunaofindia.nic.in/PDFVolumes/memoirs/008/02/0069-0089.pdf" year="1925">Prashad 1925</bibRefCitation>
: 74: pl. 13, fig. 8); Major L. W. Wilmer, leg.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="type material">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type material.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Lectotype, by designation of 
<bibRefCitation author="Prashad, B" journalOrPublisher="Nature in Singapore" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://faunaofindia.nic.in/PDFVolumes/memoirs/008/02/0069-0089.pdf" refId="B26" refString="Prashad, B, 1925. Revision of the Indian Ampullariidae. Memoirs of the Indian Museum 8(2): 69-89, pls. 13-15. http://faunaofindia.nic.in/PDFVolumes/memoirs/008/02/0069-0089.pdf" title="Revision of the Indian Ampullariidae. Memoirs of the Indian Museum 8 (2): 69 - 89, pls. 13 - 15." url="http://faunaofindia.nic.in/PDFVolumes/memoirs/008/02/0069-0089.pdf" year="1925">Prashad (1925</bibRefCitation>
: 74: pl. 13, fig. 8): NZSI M.2445 (registered 10 January 1894). Paralectotypes: NZSI M.25082/5 (registered 24 September 2001, 2 spms); 7 additional specimens noted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nevill, G" journalOrPublisher="Archives of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://media.api.aucklandmuseum.com/id/media/p/1bf9a093da0f3bd874f966ce7d0483bf7904668f?rendering=original.pdf" refId="B21" refString="Nevill, G, 1877. Catalogue of Mollusca in the Indian Museum, Calcutta. Fasciculus E. Indian Museum, Calcutta [= Kolkata], [4] + 42 pp. http://media.api.aucklandmuseum.com/id/media/p/1bf9a093da0f3bd874f966ce7d0483bf7904668f?rendering=original.pdf" title="Catalogue of Mollusca in the Indian Museum, Calcutta. Fasciculus E. Indian Museum, Calcutta [= Kolkata], [4] + 42 pp." url="http://media.api.aucklandmuseum.com/id/media/p/1bf9a093da0f3bd874f966ce7d0483bf7904668f?rendering=original.pdf" year="1877">Nevill (1877</bibRefCitation>
: 4), not found in NZSI in 2014 (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3940.1.1" author="Cowie, RH" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 92" refId="B8" refString="Cowie, RH, 2015. The recent apple snails of Africa and Asia (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Ampullariidae: Afropomus, Forbesopomus, Lanistes, Pila, Saulea): a nomenclatural and type catalogue. The apple snails of the Americas: addenda and corrigenda. Zootaxa 3940 (1): 1 - 92, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3940.1.1" title="The recent apple snails of Africa and Asia (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Ampullariidae: Afropomus, Forbesopomus, Lanistes, Pila, Saulea): a nomenclatural and type catalogue. The apple snails of the Americas: addenda and corrigenda." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3940.1.1" volume="3940" year="2015">Cowie 2015</bibRefCitation>
: 52).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="shell dimensions">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Shell dimensions.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Lectotype: SH 35.6 mm, SW 29.9 mm, AH 25.1 mm, AW 19.6 mm. Paralectotypes: SH 27.0, 33.2 mm, SW 24.4, 27.7 mm, AH 20.3, 23.0 mm, AW 16.3, 18.9 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<bibRefCitation author="Nevill, G" journalOrPublisher="Archives of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://media.api.aucklandmuseum.com/id/media/p/1bf9a093da0f3bd874f966ce7d0483bf7904668f?rendering=original.pdf" refId="B21" refString="Nevill, G, 1877. Catalogue of Mollusca in the Indian Museum, Calcutta. Fasciculus E. Indian Museum, Calcutta [= Kolkata], [4] + 42 pp. http://media.api.aucklandmuseum.com/id/media/p/1bf9a093da0f3bd874f966ce7d0483bf7904668f?rendering=original.pdf" title="Catalogue of Mollusca in the Indian Museum, Calcutta. Fasciculus E. Indian Museum, Calcutta [= Kolkata], [4] + 42 pp." url="http://media.api.aucklandmuseum.com/id/media/p/1bf9a093da0f3bd874f966ce7d0483bf7904668f?rendering=original.pdf" year="1877">Nevill (1877</bibRefCitation>
: 4; 1885: 2) listed eight specimens from &quot;Near Dum-Dum&quot; collected by Major L. W. Wilmer and two specimens from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Siliguri”">&quot;Siliguri&quot;</normalizedToken>
collected by Colonel G. B. Mainwaring. 
<bibRefCitation author="Prashad, B" journalOrPublisher="Nature in Singapore" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://faunaofindia.nic.in/PDFVolumes/memoirs/008/02/0069-0089.pdf" refId="B26" refString="Prashad, B, 1925. Revision of the Indian Ampullariidae. Memoirs of the Indian Museum 8(2): 69-89, pls. 13-15. http://faunaofindia.nic.in/PDFVolumes/memoirs/008/02/0069-0089.pdf" title="Revision of the Indian Ampullariidae. Memoirs of the Indian Museum 8 (2): 69 - 89, pls. 13 - 15." url="http://faunaofindia.nic.in/PDFVolumes/memoirs/008/02/0069-0089.pdf" year="1925">Prashad (1925</bibRefCitation>
: 74, pl. 13, fig. 8) subsequently unambiguously selected one of the syntypes from Dumdum as the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Type-specimen”">&quot;Type-specimen&quot;</normalizedToken>
, thereby designating the lectotype and restricting the type locality, as above (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3940.1.1" author="Cowie, RH" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 92" refId="B8" refString="Cowie, RH, 2015. The recent apple snails of Africa and Asia (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Ampullariidae: Afropomus, Forbesopomus, Lanistes, Pila, Saulea): a nomenclatural and type catalogue. The apple snails of the Americas: addenda and corrigenda. Zootaxa 3940 (1): 1 - 92, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3940.1.1" title="The recent apple snails of Africa and Asia (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Ampullariidae: Afropomus, Forbesopomus, Lanistes, Pila, Saulea): a nomenclatural and type catalogue. The apple snails of the Americas: addenda and corrigenda." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3940.1.1" volume="3940" year="2015">Cowie 2015</bibRefCitation>
: 42). Only two paralectotypes were found in NZSI in 2014. 
<bibRefCitation author="Nevill, G" journalOrPublisher="Archives of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://media.api.aucklandmuseum.com/id/media/p/1bf9a093da0f3bd874f966ce7d0483bf7904668f?rendering=original.pdf" refId="B21" refString="Nevill, G, 1877. Catalogue of Mollusca in the Indian Museum, Calcutta. Fasciculus E. Indian Museum, Calcutta [= Kolkata], [4] + 42 pp. http://media.api.aucklandmuseum.com/id/media/p/1bf9a093da0f3bd874f966ce7d0483bf7904668f?rendering=original.pdf" title="Catalogue of Mollusca in the Indian Museum, Calcutta. Fasciculus E. Indian Museum, Calcutta [= Kolkata], [4] + 42 pp." url="http://media.api.aucklandmuseum.com/id/media/p/1bf9a093da0f3bd874f966ce7d0483bf7904668f?rendering=original.pdf" year="1877">Nevill (1877</bibRefCitation>
: 4) considered the shell to be almost intermediate between 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. globosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="globosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A. globosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. maura" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="maura">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A. maura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but 
<bibRefCitation author="Prashad, B" journalOrPublisher="Nature in Singapore" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://faunaofindia.nic.in/PDFVolumes/memoirs/008/02/0069-0089.pdf" refId="B26" refString="Prashad, B, 1925. Revision of the Indian Ampullariidae. Memoirs of the Indian Museum 8(2): 69-89, pls. 13-15. http://faunaofindia.nic.in/PDFVolumes/memoirs/008/02/0069-0089.pdf" title="Revision of the Indian Ampullariidae. Memoirs of the Indian Museum 8 (2): 69 - 89, pls. 13 - 15." url="http://faunaofindia.nic.in/PDFVolumes/memoirs/008/02/0069-0089.pdf" year="1925">Prashad (1925</bibRefCitation>
: 74) considered it &quot;as closely allied to 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. conica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="conica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. conica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;. It does not seem appropriate to treat it as a distinct subspecies (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Code</emphasis>
, Art 45.6.4), and therefore, following 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3940.1.1" author="Cowie, RH" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 92" refId="B8" refString="Cowie, RH, 2015. The recent apple snails of Africa and Asia (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Ampullariidae: Afropomus, Forbesopomus, Lanistes, Pila, Saulea): a nomenclatural and type catalogue. The apple snails of the Americas: addenda and corrigenda. Zootaxa 3940 (1): 1 - 92, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3940.1.1" title="The recent apple snails of Africa and Asia (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Ampullariidae: Afropomus, Forbesopomus, Lanistes, Pila, Saulea): a nomenclatural and type catalogue. The apple snails of the Americas: addenda and corrigenda." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3940.1.1" volume="3940" year="2015">Cowie (2015</bibRefCitation>
: 42), who followed 
<bibRefCitation author="Prashad, B" journalOrPublisher="Nature in Singapore" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/31810945" refId="B25" refString="Prashad, B, 1923. Revision of Kobelt's nomenclature of the Indian Ampullariidae. Journal and Proceedings of the Asiatic Society of Bengal, New Series 18 (10 [for 1922]): 585-591. https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/31810945" title="Revision of Kobelt's nomenclature of the Indian Ampullariidae. Journal and Proceedings of the Asiatic Society of Bengal, New Series 18 (10 [for 1922]): 585 - 591." url="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/31810945" year="1923">Prashad (1923</bibRefCitation>
: 587), we here treat it as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swainson" authorityYear="1822" class="Gastropoda" family="Ampullariidae" genus="Ampullaria" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ampullaria globosa" order="Testacea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="globosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ampullaria globosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Swainson.
</paragraph>
